        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Never reset an MCB with wet hands, standing on a wet floor, or if the panel is in an area that has been exposed to water. The panel box itself might be energised from the incoming supply. Always use dry hands, stand on a dry surface, and use a torch — never your phone camera flash — to illuminate the panel. If in doubt, call an electrician." }
